A 19-year-old man has been arrested for the murder of a woman who was found with her dressed stuffed in her mouth. ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Police spokesman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said the body of Cindy Bailey, 40, was discovered under a tree next to her KwaMashu home on Friday. She appeared to have been strangled. “A post-mortem will be conducted to confirm the cause of death and if the deceased was raped,” said Mbhele. 

 Acting provincial commissioner Major General Bheki Langa commended the swift reaction of police which led to the arrest.  “We will fight gender-based violence will up most solemnity to ensure that the culprits are successfully prosecuted and sent to prison indefinitely,” he said. 

The man will be charged and is expected to appear in the Ntuzuma Magistrates Court soon. 

According to last year’s police crime statistics, there were 129 murders, 120 sexual offences and 112 rapes reported at the KwaMashu E police precinct. 

The Mercury